  "Notes": [
    {
      "Text": "ncurses security update",
      "Title": "Synopsis",
      "Type": "General"
    },
    {
      "Text": "An update for ncurses is now available for openEuler-20.03-LTS-SP4",
      "Title": "Summary",
      "Type": "General"
    },
    {
      "Text": "The ncurses (new curses) library is a free software emulation of  curses in System V Release 4.0 (SVr4), and more. It uses terminfo  format, supports pads and color and multiple highlights and forms  characters and function-key mapping, and has all the other SVr4-curses  enhancements over BSD curses. SVr4 curses became the basis of X/Open Curses.\n\nSecurity Fix(es):\n\nThe infocmp command-line tool in ncurses before 6.5-20251213 has a stack-based buffer overflow in analyze_string in progs/infocmp.c.(CVE-2025-69720)",
      "Title": "Description",
      "Type": "General"
    },
    {
      "Text": "An update for ncurses is now available for openEuler-20.03-LTS-SP4.\n\nopenEuler Security has rated this update as having a security impact of high. A Common Vunlnerability Scoring System(CVSS)base score,which gives a detailed severity rating, is available for each vulnerability from the CVElink(s) in the References section.",
      "Title": "Topic",
      "Type": "General"
    },
    {
      "Text": "High",
      "Title": "Severity",
      "Type": "General"
    },
    {
      "Text": "ncurses",
      "Title": "Affected Component",
      "Type": "General"
    }
  ],
